-- Teen Armed With Swords Takes Children Hostage in Nursery in Eastern France
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2010-12-13T11:01:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/teen-armed-with-swords-takes-children-hostage-in-nursery-in-eastern-france.html
A young man took nursery school
children hostage this morning in Besancon, eastern France, a
spokeswoman for the local city hall said.  The 17-year-old, armed with two swords, is still holding
six children captive, radio station  France Info reported . The
teenager initially took 20 children hostage, France Info said.  The city hall spokeswoman, who declined to be named, was
unable to give more details.  Police have surrounded the school and negotiators are in
contact with the hostage-taker by telephone, Agence France-
Presse said. The class from which the hostages were taken was
made up of kids between four and six years old, AFP said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Rudy Ruitenberg  in Paris at 
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 